               <msContents>
                  <summary>FF. 1r-32r: Qerelos On the Orthodox Faith (De recta fide), Bä’ntä Haymanot Rǝt‘ǝt; FF. 32r-88r:  Qerelos The Beauty of the News, Sena Zena;  Ff. 88v-131r: Qerelos That Christ is One, Kama aḥadu Krestos. Ff. 131r-132v: Homily by Theodotus of Ancyra; Ff. 132v-133v: Homily by Cyril of Alexandria; Ff. 133v-134v:  Homily by Severus of Synnada; Ff. 134v-135v:  Homily by Acacius of Melitene; FF. 135v-136v: Homily by Juvenalius of Jerusalem; Ff. 136v-138r: Homily by Cyril of Alexandria; Ff. 138r-139r: Homily by Rheginus of Constantinople; Ff. 139r-140v: Homily by Cyril of Alexandria; Ff. 140v-141r: Homily by Eusiebius of Heraclea; Ff. 141r-142v; Homily by Theodotus of Ancyra; Ff. 142v-143r: Homily by Firmus of Caesarea; Ff. 143r-143v: Epistle of the Synod of Ephesus to John of Antioch; Ff. 143v-144r: Homily by Cyril of Alexandria; Ff. 144r-145r: Epistle of John of Antioch to Cyril of Alexandria; Ff. 145r-147r: Epistle of Cyril of Alexandria to John of Antioch; Ff. 147r-151r: Homily by Epiphanius of Cyprus; Ff. 151r-151v: Homily by Epiphanius of Cyprus on the Trinity; Ff. 151v-155v: Homily by Proclus of Cyzicus; Ff. 155v-161v: Homily by Severianus of Gabala; Ff. 161v-162r: The Faith of Gregory Thaumaturgus; Ff. 162r-165r: The first homily of Cyril of Alexandria on Melchisedec; Ff. 165r-167v: The second homily of Cyril of Alexandria on Melchisedec; Ff. 167v-168v: Homily by a Sage on Melchisedec; F. 168v: On the 318 Orthodox Fathers; Ff. 168v-169r: On the Nativity and Life of Our Lord. Ff. 170r-171v: Confession of faith, written in later hand.</summary>
